Hey, thanks for reading- and for running the numbers on this! This is actually intentional, though I think that may not have come through as clearly as I'd thought it would. (Or even not at all, maybe- I do have to admit I was kind of counting on this going largely unnoticed, haha.) I was hoping that combined with the note at the beginning the incongruency between the justification of  and numbers that didn't really work (such as the maximal water depth being far too small, as well,) would give off the impression of something being really wrong rather than reading as an author oversight, but thinking about it now I may not have gone about it the best way. One of my earlier drafts solved this specific problem by mentioning a decrease in marine wildlife around the rig, which in hindsight might have been a good idea to keep- the intended implication here is that this thing is getting a lot more, well, food, than it seems at first glance.







